cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network (DCNN) for writer identification using online handwritten Chinese characters. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a data-augmentation method named DropStroke to enrich personal handwriting and improve the generalization of the model. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an end-to-end text-independent writer-identification system using deep learning techniques. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper discusses the identification of writers based on their handwriting, which can be considered a form of information retrieval. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with the identification of writers based on their written language, which falls under the scope of computational linguistics.
